methods.expandDuplicates:
Expands entries values from chunkToExpand in-place, using keyRunLengths to determine how many copies. The
 keyRunLengths chunk is parallel to the original chunkToExpand; it is never modified.

*Overload 1*  
  :param expandedSize: (int) - the sum of all entries in keyRunLengths
  :param chunkToExpand: (io.deephaven.chunk.WritableChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.chunk.attributes.Any>) - the values to expand in-place (this writable chunk must have capacity >= expandedSize)
  :param keyRunLengths: (io.deephaven.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.chunk.attributes.ChunkLengths>) - the key run-lengths parallel to chunkToExpand
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param expandedSize: int
  :param chunkToExpand: io.deephaven.chunk.WritableFloatChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.chunk.attributes.Any>
  :param keyRunLengths: io.deephaven.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.chunk.attributes.ChunkLengths>
